caption:
2x01 - Do You Know How to Dispose of a Body?
Eve is reeling from her act of violence against Villanelle and doesn’t know whether she is alive or dead. A paranoid and severely injured Villanelle manages to get herself to the hospital for treatment. Carolyn approaches Eve with an intriguing opportunity.

2x02 -  Nice and Neat
Carolyn introduces Eve to her new team before Eve briefs them on the Villanelle case. Villanelle, needing to lie low while she recovers, finds a good Samaritan to take her in and care for her.

summary: Thinking about the season two teaser trailer of Killing Eve... though everything about it is overwhelmingly beautiful my...
body:
Thinking about the season two teaser trailer of Killing Eve… though everything about it is overwhelmingly beautiful my favorite thing about it is the anticipation of Eve and Villanelle seeing each other again. I was rewatching 1x08 a couple days ago and got to the part where Eve flies to Paris, stands in front of Villanelle’s apartment door and tries to find a way to open it to get inside but can’t until the old lady asks her if she would like a key. And then Eve steps inside and obviously doesn’t find Villanelle until she actually does meet her, which surprises them both, Villanelle being just as thrilled about Eve’s presence:

The season two teaser trailer toys with that concept so much that it doesn’t reinterpret but deepen whatever it is these two see in each other. I seriously have nothing new or witty to say I’m just unable to contain my Feelings because this shit’s poetic. Like, reintroducing the same visual motif like an interlude (even though in the show these scenes could have a different context you never know). Really shows just how particular Eve and Villanelle’s dynamic is. From the first contact to reciprocated gaze (THE WAY THIS IS PACKAGED OKAY):
